                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1679: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-20T00:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 20, 1933—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received February 20—11:14
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>169. Your 59, February 18, 1 p.m. I discussed matter with British Minister and
                    Secretary of Italian Legation this evening informing them confidentially of
                    Department’s views. Lampson has not yet communicated Chinese note to London. He
                    will do so tomorrow with arguments pro and con and recommending against Chinese
                    proposal on the ground that further postponement would be disadvantageous to
                    China as harming projects already planned under British indemnity arrangement.
                    Italian is informing his Minister [of] our attitude and of Lampson’s proposed
                    line. Italian said Ciano<note n="43" xml:id="d720fn43">Count Galeazzo Ciano di
                        Cortellazzo, Italian Minister in China.</note> had originally informed his
                    Government that personally he saw no reason why Italy should not make an
                    affirmative reply to Chinese proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
